main event: A civilian observed a UFO for 105 minutes on August 3, 1965 in Brooklyn, New York.
interesting points: The object was observed both visually and auditorily.
The observer filled out a UFO report form (Form 57A) which was sent to the Air Force, but it was returned due to insufficient data.
The Air Force requested additional information to complete the investigation, but the report was never returned.
The Air Force concluded that there was insufficient data to evaluate the case and stated they would reopen it if further data was received.
The report appears to be part of the Project Blue Book UFO investigation program.
